The paper deals with large-scale, distributed graph clustering, which involves processing and analyzing big data. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses two established formalizations of the internally-dense-externally-sparse principle, modularity and map equation, which are related to machine learning and data mining. Hence, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper presents two versions of a simple distributed algorithm to optimize both measures, which involves computational techniques and algorithms. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible sub-categories.
